* Returns a new <code>List</code> containing all elements from the specified
* <code>Collection</code> in the same iteration order.
* This method is useful when you want to create a mutable copy of an existing
* collection. For example:
* <pre>
* {@code
* List<String> names = new ArrayList<>(createNames());
* }
* </pre>
* See also:
* <ul>
*   <li>{@link java.util.Collections#unmodifiableList(List)}</li>
*   <li>{@link java.util.ArrayList}</li>
* </ul>
*
* @param collection the source collection
* @return a new mutable list containing the elements of the collection